00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.300
Sword Art Online: The Beginning
Sponsored by IBM
 - Future Possibilities Brought about by Technology -

00:00:04.900 --> 00:00:08.700
[Yuriko Furunaga, Director, Cloud Marketing, IBM Japan]
Right now in 2016, we are entering the future.

00:00:08.739 --> 00:00:11.099
This is what we feel.

00:00:11.099 --> 00:00:15.300
Under such circumstances, what types of changes can technology bring to your business?

00:00:15.349 --> 00:00:20.100
How can our latest technologies at IBM make creative contributions?

00:00:20.179 --> 00:00:25.100
We are always looking for opportunities to answer these questions.

00:00:25.140 --> 00:00:30.300
[Yukiko Yamaguchi, Manager, Communications &amp; Brand Experience, Marketing &amp; Communications, IBM Japan]
Experience the possibilities technology can bring to the future.

00:00:31.489 --> 00:00:38.500
The story that we selected to make that happen is Sword Art Online,

00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:44.800
which is a fictional virtual reality game to be released in 2022.

00:00:44.820 --> 00:00:51.800
How can we use the latest technologies we have today to express the world of Sword Art Online?

00:00:51.830 --> 00:00:55.070
It is a challenge that no one has experienced before.

00:00:55.070 --> 00:00:58.120
It is a challenge that no one has experienced before.

00:00:58.120 --> 00:01:05.400
[Reki Kawahara, Author of Sword Art Online]
I felt strongly that it was possible the story I dreamed up about 15 years ago could eventually come true.

00:01:05.410 --> 00:01:09.900
This project, from the time of its release, garnered a lot of media attention, as well as a tremendous response on social media.

